text.__SUMMARY__: Asparagus simulans is a species of Asparagus native to Madagascar. Asparagus simulans was described by English botanist John Gilbert Baker in 1875.
text.Synonyms:
Asparagus madagascariensis Baker
Asparagus rusciformis Brongn. ex H.Perrier
Asparagus ternatus Brongn. ex H.Perrier
text.References:
Baker, J. Linn. Soc., Bot. 14: 609 (1875)
